To combine the fractions, add the numerators (since the denominators are the same):

\[
\frac{-11x}{5} + \frac{7x}{5}
= \frac{-11x + 7x}{5}
= \frac{-4x}{5}.
\]

To add the fractions, combine like denominators:

\[
- \frac{9}{19} + \frac{17}{19}
= \frac{-9 + 17}{19}
= \frac{8}{19}.
\]

To subtract, combine over the common denominator d:

\[
-\frac{8}{d}-\frac{3}{d}
=\frac{-8-3}{d}
=\frac{-11}{d}.
\]

To combine, use the common denominator \(v\):  
\[
-\frac{29}{v}-\frac{26}{v}
=\frac{-29-26}{v}
=\frac{-55}{v}
=-\frac{55}{v}.
\]

To subtract, combine like terms over the common denominator 11:

\[
\frac{12d}{11} - \frac{9d}{11}
= \frac{12d - 9d}{11}
= \frac{3d}{11}.
\]

To multiply, first factor and cancel common factors:

\[
- \frac{3}{14} \cdot \frac{7}{12}
= - \frac{3 \cdot 7}{14 \cdot 12}
= - \frac{3 \cdot \cancel{7}}{\;2\cdot\cancel{7}\;\cdot 12}
= - \frac{3}{2\cdot 12}
= - \frac{3}{24}
= - \frac{1}{8}.
\]

So the simplified result is \(-\tfrac{1}{8}\).
